alpha01a.1.description:
Golly, we are officially in the alpha milestone!

See more information about this mod (bugs, workarounds, configs, etc) in the Cuphead thread in the Archipelago Discord.

*Note: Some YAML settings have changed format, check your yaml!*

**Not compatible with any version older than alpha01!**

### What's new in alpha01

- We are in alpha, baby!
- Ms. Chalice is playable now!
- Lot's of logic issues fixed
- Huge project restructure with tests which improves the code quality to reduce the likelihood of rookie mistake bugs. (nerd stuffs)

Have fun, and take care!

This hotfix fixes the example yaml. It should not affect functionality.

**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/compare/preview03f...alpha01a.1

alpha02a.description:
Hot Dog! We got another big release!

See more information about this mod (bugs, workarounds, configs, etc) in the Cuphead thread in the Archipelago Discord.

*Note: Some YAML settings have changed format, check your yaml!*

WARNING: This is in alpha, just be aware that bugs do exist in things that are in early development!

**NOTE: This is not compatible with any apworld version older than alpha02!**

### What's new in alpha02?

- Level Shuffle!
- Better Logic.
- Better Weapon logic.
- Lots of logic fixes including Chalice Logic.
- Another project restructure with more stringent tests that improve the code quality to reduce the likelihood of more rookie mistake bugs. (geek stuffs)

### Known Issues
- While a lot of the Chalice logic got resolved and fixed, there is probably more missing chalice logic hanging around.

Have fun, and take care!
alpha02a.title: APWorld alpha02a

alpha02b.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

### Revision

This revision fixes default YAML template not working (and `level_placements` not working correctly).
alpha02b.title: APWorld alpha02b

alpha02c.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

### Revision

This revision fixes option sanitization, which ironically was making the options insane instead. This fixes the "requested value 'False' not found" errors. This also fixes options being wrongfully disabled as well.

This revision also fixes the King's Leap locations not getting excluded correctly when the locations are disabled.

alpha02f.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

### Revision

This revision:
- Fixes a mistake with the options resolution with the `mode` option.
- Fixed King Dice miniboss levels not being properly mapped which broke them being shuffled.
- Adds an option to enable or disable King Dice miniboss shuffling.
alpha02f.title: APWorld alpha02f

alpha02g.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

**WARNING:** Older clients are not compatible with this APWorld when generated with secret checks on! Make sure you update the client to [alpha02d](https://github.com/JKLeckr/CupheadArchipelagoMod/releases/tag/alpha02d) or newer.

### Revision

This revision:
- Added official Python 3.13 support (if you do not know what that means, then don't worry about it).
- Adds missing secret check location for Doggone Dogfight.
alpha02g.title: APWorld alpha02g

alpha02h.1.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

### Revision

This revision improves distribution for contract requirements. For example: Before, contract requirements set to 8 would require 2 contracts to access Isle Two, 4 to access Isle Three, and 8 to access King Dice. The new math would make the requirements 2, then 5, then 8 respectively instead.

### Hotfix

This hotfix updates the option description for `boss_secret_checks` that includes Doggone Dogfight.
alpha02h.1.title: APWorld alpha02h.1

alpha02i.1.description:
**To see notes and what's new for alpha02, see [alpha02a](https://github.com/JKLeckr/Archipelago-cuphead/releases/tag/alpha02a)**

### Revision

This revision renames the options module, which coincidentally fixes it not working with WebHost.
This change was ported from the project restructure happening in the dev branch for alpha03.

### Hotfix

This hotfix fixes the template yaml and some of the options.
alpha02i.1.title: APWorld alpha02i.1

preview02j.description:
### Please Read This Before Downloading

This is a preview. Not an official release. While more options work, your mileage may vary.
Do not expect this to fully work correctly. This is mainly to show the fruits of labor.

See more information about this apworld (bugs, workarounds, configs, etc) in the Cuphead thread in the Archipelago Discord.

**Note: From preview01, option names have changed, check your yaml!**

### What's new highlights for preview02

- Freemove Isles
- Ability Rando
- Better grade checks
- Max health settings
- Filler Item Weights
- DeathLink
- Traps are broken in this version. :(
- A good number of bug fixes and improvements

This revision fixes broken apworld and reachability.
preview02j.title: APWorld Second Preview (preview02j)

preview03f.description:
### Please Read This Before Downloading

This is a preview. While more things work compared to last time, there are still bugs hanging around and maybe new ones are introduced.
Do not expect a fully working product. The previews are mainly to show the fruits of labor.

See more information about this mod (bugs, workarounds, configs, etc) in the Cuphead thread in the Archipelago Discord.

**Note: Options have changed significantly since preview02, check your existing yaml before using it with this version!**

### What's new highlights for preview03

- Delicious Last Course Support (Ms. Chalice isn't available for now 😢)
- Multiple goals options
- More settings for requirements
- More client config options
- No traps still 😢
- Some polished surprises
- I don't want to look at the commit history to see what else has changed (This is a big update)
- A several bug fixes and improvements

Have fun, and take care!

### Revision

This revision should prevent rogue goal locations (this time).
This revision also changes how the APWorld version is written to spoiler (it's better).
preview03f.title: APWorld Third Preview (preview03f)
